Picture Day is Coming- September 17th & 18th!!
Pictures will be taken during the school day- 8:30 am - 12:30 pm. Students with the last names beginning A-L will be on Thursday and M-Z on Friday. Preschool will take theirs on Friday. If your child is a remote learner, they can come in anytime between 1:00 pm - 2:30 pm either day. All students will need their pictures taken for the yearbook. Forms will be sent home next week. You may order pictures online- mylifetouch.com with the event code EVTHRZVDT. If you have any questions, please contact Ms. Kelly!

post_text:
Attention PARENTS of Kindergarten, 2nd, and 6th Graders:
Time is flying by and we just want to remind you that Physicals and updated shot records need to be completed and turned in to the Front Office by or before Oct. 15th, 2020. This is mandated by the State.

Kindergarteners are required to have a Physical, up to date shots, Dental and Eye exams.
2nd Graders are required to have Dental Exams.
6th Graders are required to have a School Physical (Sports physical are NOT be acceptable), a Tdap and a Meningococcal vaccine, and a Dental exam.

If you have any questions you can call the Office.

post_text:
During remote learning, St. Anne Grade School will still be offering Breakfast and Lunch options for our students. If you would like to order a breakfast/lunch for either pick up or delivery please fill out this google form. We do ask that you, for planning purposes, fill this form out one time for the week. Also, one form may be used for each St. Anne Grade School Family. A new form must be submitted no later then Sunday evening at 7:00 p.m. for delivery the next day.

Breakfast cost: $1.25 per day, .30 Reduced. Lunch cost: $2.65 per day/ .40 reduced. Some students may also qualify for free breakfast and lunch and will not be charged. Lunch Delivery will begin on Monday August 22, 2020 and will contain that days lunch and the following days breakfast.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeMeSE2c3VbBt2fm4CgJvxcS1dqNu2xPCdSM8-2txcUa3tzNw/viewform?usp=sf_link

shared_text:
St. Anne Grade School PTO - District #256
April 29 at 4:24 PM ·

We are working with The Write Stuff to host a supply kit sale. $3 from each kit sold will be donated to the PTO and will go towards campus improvement at the school.

Go to www.write-stuff.com/storefront/school/stanne and start shopping. Kits will be delivered to the school and will be ready for pick up on the day of registration. We extended the sale! Free shipping to the school now ends on May 22nd.

Pictured is a sample kit. Each kit will have the brands and quantities specified by your child's teacher and comes with personalized labels. You may customize your child's kit by adding or deleting items.

If you have any questions please message the PTO Facebook page or email Ashley at ashleychildress613@gmail.com

Good afternoon St. Anne Families.

We were notified a few moments ago that the Governors Office will be issuing a mandatory school closure for all public schools in the State of Illinois beginning on Tuesday, March 17th and running until March 30th. More details regarding this mandatory closure and how it affects St. Anne Schools will be forthcoming from me in the coming days. Just a reminder, as of today, school will be in session on Monday, March 16th but will be closed beginning Tuesday, March 17th through March 30th as mandated by the Governor of Illinois.

Thank you and have a good weekend.

#TheSAGSway

post_text:
March 12, 2020

St. Anne Schools Families,

Good afternoon. At this time, there are NO reported cases of COVID-19 in our area and Illinois public schools in our area are still open for business. Even so, it is extremely important for schools to finalize plans in case we are forced to close due to this virus. As a result, St. Anne schools will have an early dismissal tomorrow, Friday, March 13, 2020 to allow our faculty and staff necessary time to plan for possible future emergency school closures related to the COVID-19 pandemic. St. Anne High School will dismiss at 11:05 a.m. and St. Anne Grade School will dismiss at 11:25 a.m. tomorrow, Friday, March 13, 2020. At this time, we plan to be in a regular session on Monday, March 16, 2020.

We appreciate your flexibility and understanding regarding this situation and as always, we will update you with any new changes.

Charlie Stegall, Superintendent of Schools
St. Anne #256 and #302
